0041|- [HelpText]
0042|#POWERS <data> / POW_VARS=<List_of_variables>  DEGREE=<d>
S   |        <    >            <                 >         < >
0043|*computes all possible products of powers up to degree <d>
S   |                                                       < >
0044|*of variables in POW_VARS as (new) variables.
0045|*Since the number of new variables may be high, the scope of the
0046|*data file must often be extended by FILE EXPAND operation before using
0047|*POWERS.
0049|*Example:
0050|*POWERS D2 / POW_VARS=Height(H),Weight(W) DEGREE=3
0051|*creates and computes variables H2, H1W1, W2, H3, H2W1, H1W2, W3
0052|*where, for example, H2W1 is Height^2*Weight.
0054|*The types of new variables are given by TYPE=<1|2|4|8> (default is 8).
S   |                                              <       >
0055|*The maximum # of power variables is 10 and the maximum degree is 20.
0056|*Too long names (over 8 characters) like A1B2C3D4F5 are presented as
0057|*X12345. Actual expressions like A^3*B^2*C are given as extensions of
0058|*names.
0060|*POWERS is a tool for generating variables for polynomial regression
0061|*analysis and its generalizations (to be computed by LINREG, for
0062|*example).
